* gûbur :: nominal :: a Sapient of low estate, a disesteemed person

* -îm :: adverbial suffix :: -ly
  - works with nominals, adjectivals, etc, etc

* -then :: direct speech clitic suffix, direct speech marker :: quotes a word, makes a word be felt as a spoken thing 
  Follows the first word of the direct speech: /...spelâleth
  kafâlen-then Marishôdh/ :: ..."He said "I go to Marish".

* kefet :: nominal :: visible spectrum light
  Although technically the word for photonic energy, kefet came to be
  used preferentially in the Low Canals region of Mars over the older
  word for visible light, fon. Practically, either may be used
  indifferently.

* fon :: nominal :: light, brightness
  Although technically the word for photonic energy, kefet came to be
  used preferentially in the Low Canals region of Mars over the older
  word for visible light, fon. Practically, either may be used
  indifferently.

* lay :: verbal :: radiate
  In J. the sun, the moons, the stars do not shine, they radiate.
  /lay/ can take an object, namely the heat, light, or whatever that
  the object is radiating.

