* am :: the appositive preposition 
  - previously called the appositive interposition
  - usage example: /tek am hûdhax/, that shit you talk, what-you-talk
    appositivePrep turd
  - note the parallel(s) between /am/ and /ken...wel/ on the one hand,
    and /-thor/ and /koi/ on the other
  - RULE the appositive preposition and therefore any appositive that
    it points to can occur after almost any nominal in a manner quite
    unlike English

