* ken-...wel :: circumposition :: parenthetical and relative clause marker
  - example 1 :: /homin, ken-tethôdh shê spelâlen wel,/ et cetera :: the genus
    homo specimen that I was talking to :: (literally) the human, that
    I was speaking to him/her, et cetera
  --- the him/her is what's called */a resumptive pronoun/*
  --- the resumptive pronoun is suffixed with a hyphen to /ken-/
  -- example 2 :: /homin, ken-teth shê î tatameth/ :: the human, who
     was his/her father, et cetera :: the human (he was his/her
     father) :: the human, who he was her father, 

