* -âl :: suffix :: finite verbal marker

* -en :: suffix :: nominal and verbal plural marker

* -em :: suffix :: 1s possessive suffix
- note :: -en is the 1s finite verbal marker, in addition to an
  identical form being the universal plural marker
* -eps :: suffix :: 2s possessive and finite verbal suffix
* -eth :: suffix :: 3s sapient possessive and finite verbal suffix
* -os :: suffix :: 3s insapient possessive and finite verbal suffix 
* -emen :: suffix :: 2p possessive verbal suffix
* -enen :: suffix :: 2p finite verbal suffix
* -epsen :: suffix :: 2p possessive and finite verbal suffix
* -ethen :: suffix :: 3p sapient possessive and finite verbal suffix
* -osen :: suffix :: 3p insapient possessive and finite verbal suffix

* TABLE :: Jagarôth verbal suffixes and personal possessive suffixed 
  |--------------+----------+------------|
  | person &     | finite v | possessive |
  | number &     | suffix   | suffix     |
  | gender       |          |            |
  |--------------+----------+------------|
  | 1s           | -en      | -em        |
  | 1p           | -enen    | -emen      |
  | 2s           | -eps     | -eps       |
  | 2p           | -epsen   | -epsen     |
  | 3s sapient   | -eth     | -eth       |
  | 3p sapient   | -ethen   | -ethen     |
  | 3s insapient | -os      | -os        |
  | 3p insapient | -osen    | -osen      |
  |--------------+----------+------------|

* zed :: personal pronoun, reflexive :: himself, herself, themselves
  - /-ed/ :: suffixed form, finite verbal and possessive

* totekek :: personal pronoun, reciprocal :: each other
  - from /tot/ (one) + /kek/ (another)
  - suffix form: /-ek/

* hemp :: personal pronoun, unspecified and impersonal (which is one
  - translation :: contextual

* kek :: adjectival :: other

* -thor :: suffix :: and, the conjunctive suffix
  - conjoins nominals, adjectivals, verbals, adverbials, etc.
  - does not conjoin clauses
  - /koi/ conjoins clauses

* -sest :: suffix :: but, the disjunctive suffix
  - ??? needed as "but" counterpart to /koi/ "and" for clauses
  - disjoins nominals, adjectivals, verbals, adverbials, etc.
  - does not disjoin clauses

* ??? :: disjunctive conjunction:: but
  - joins clauses with a meaning of /but.../


* krânik :: conjuction :: although, even though
  - clause level conjunction, concessive 
  - example usage sentence :: /krânik teth î vâv, tethot vê kornâlen
  bor/
  - although she copula woman she-ACC FUTURE fuck-FINITE-1s
  - Although she is a woman, I will not fuck her.

* korn :: verbal :: to fuck

* vê :: adverbial tense marker :: future tense, in the future
  - preposed to the verb

* vêpep :: adverbial tense marker :: in the near future, immediately
  - adverbial tense particle /vê/ "in the future" + diminutive
  - preposed to the verb

* vêded :: adverbial tense marker :: in the distant future.
  - adverbial particle "in the future" + augmentative
  - preposed to the verb

* rê :: adverbial present tense marker :: in the present
  - preposed to the verb

* rêpep :: adverbial tense marker :: in the present instant
  - /rê/ /in the present/ +  /pep/ diminutive
  - preposed to the verb

* rêded :: adverbial :: in the present age (in the present long period of time)
  - /rê/ in the present + ded augmentative
  - preposed to the verb

* shê :: adverbial tense marker :: in the past
  - preposed to the verb

* shêpep :: adverbial: tense marker :: in the (relatively) recent past
  - adverbial particle shê + diminutive -pep
  - "in the past"-DIMUNITIVE
  - preposed to the verb

* shêded :: adverbial :: in the (relatively) distant past
  - adverbial particle shê + augmentative -ded
  - "in the past"-AUGMENTATIVE
  - preposed to the verb

* skêdhin :: nominal :: vampire

* jed :: adverb :: already 
  - denotes completed, finished actions
  - /jed qîzâlen/ "I already pissed" :: /shêpep qîzâlen jed/ "I just
    now pissed already"
  - counterpart to /flet/ "still"


* hûn :: MORAL OBLIGATION modal :: must, denotes moral obligation
  - /hûn vêpep zazazâleth Wahazôdh./ :: OBLIGATION warp-FINITEVB-she/he Marish-DAT ::
    she/he must warp to Marish.
  - GRAMMATICAL NOTES
  - MODALS and ASPECTUALS
  -- NB :: modals are particles and are used instead of the modal verb +
     infinitive method of English to express grammatical mood
  -- NB :: aspectuals in J. are particles and are used to describe an
    action's relation to time and movement through time

* kin :: COUNSEL modal, should modal :: should, ought to
  /kin zazazâleth Marishôdh rêpep./ :: he/she ought to warp to Marish soon. 

* fîn :: INTENTIONALITY modal :: about to, "finna"
  - /fîn zazazâlen Wahazôdh/ :: I finna warp to Wahaz

* tên :: DESIRE modal :: denotes a desire to do something
  - pê tên zazazâleth Wahazôdh. 
  --- PAST DESIRE-modal warp-FINITE-she/he Wahaz-DAT. 
  --- she/he wanted to warp to Wahaz

* wûm :: HYPOTHETICAL modal 
  - marks a verb as pertaining to conceived or hypothetical or
    hypothesized actions
  - /wûm jûkâlen gaktâreps/ :: I should like you to dance
  - note :: the Jagarôth infinitive can receive a verbal person marker
    (which is different from the possessive person marker only in the
    1s) 

* shîm :: imperfect aspectual :: denotes ongoing action
  - but /jed/ is the perfective marker
  - /jed/ can go anywhere but /shîm/ can only go in from of the verb
  - PROBLEM :: should /jed/ be defined as /already/ instead of a
    simple grammatical word???
  - PROBLEM :: should /shîm/ be a freestanding word like /jed/ and
    thus /shîm/ would be /still/
  - how about this: /jed/ already, /flet/ still

* flet :: adverb :: still
  - indicates that the action of the utterance is ongoing
  - counterpart to /jed/ "already"



* skên :: inchoative aspectual :: denotes starting action 

* dim :: cessative aspectual :: denotes stopping action

