* te :: a kind of conjunction? what part of speech?? :: that
  - introduces a clause as a grammatical object in a sentence capable
    of being cast into a case like Nominative or Accusative
  - in other words /te/ turns the clause following it into a /thing/
  - usage :: /jûkâlen te gaktâleps/ :: /I like (the fact) that you
 dance/
   - /jûkâlen gaktâreps/ :: "I like you to dance"
  ---- this shows how i need a /hypothetical/ model
  ---- HYPOTHETICAL jûkâlen gaktâreps
  ----- but where would it go? in front of /jûkâlen/ or in front of
        /gaktâreps/ ????? :: since /jûkâlen/ is conditioned upon the
        occurence of the dancing in /gaktâreps/ it /*is*/ a
        hypothetical
  - /jûkâlen te gaktâleps/ :: "I like that you dance"
  - probably only one of these methods ought to be allowed in the more
    formal varieties of Jagarôth

* vîl :: adjectival :: yellow :: /vîlaz/ a yellow thing, smthg that is "yellowing"

* gakt :: verbal :: to dance

* jûk :: verbal :: to enjoy :: /jûkâlen gaktâr/ :: I like to dance, I like dancing

* shim :: aspectual :: the inchoative aspectual
  - /shim/ used to be /shîm/
  - shim hendâleps :: you began to have hold of/on, you grabbed
  - equivalent to /krech/
  - (!) note this word might be obsolete

* thrip :: conjunction :: clausal-level "but"               |
  - counterpart of /koi/: clausal /and/ 
  - counterpart of /-sest/ phrasal /but/

* (x) skai- :: comparative verbal prefix :: "out-" as in /outperforms/
  - skai-vîlaz :: a thing that "out-yellows", a more yellow thing
  - use the /*DATIVE*/ for the thing being compared to
  - dafodîleneps skai-vîlâlosen Rorbôdh :: the daffodils are more yellow than
    the Sun
  - I had had */skai-vîlâlethen/ above but that's incorrect; /dafodîlen/ are
    insapient
  - /dafodîl/ a daffodîl, Nominative singular, unpossessed
  - /skai-/ why doesn't it begin && end w a consonant? not a content word ::
    only content words (nominals, adjectivals, verbals, adverbials) must adhere
    to that particular phonotactic rule
    
* skaipep- :: diminutive comparative prefix :: a little /skai-/ ::
  - /dafodîleneps skaipep-vîlazâlosen Rorbôdh/ ::
  - Your daffodils are being a little more yellow than the Sun ::

* skaided- :: augmentative comparative prefix :: /skai-/ by a lot
  - skaided-layâlos Rorb kelôdhen Lûnôdh-thor
  - The Sun greatly out-radiates the stars and Luna.

* krêtor :: nominal :: electricity, electric power
  -- technological suffix /-or/, by some prehistoric process /-or/ often denotes technological objects

* thelifor :: nominal :: charity hearthstone 
  -- technological suffix /-or/, by some prehistoric process /-or/ often denotes technological objects

* nomon :: verbal :: to cook

* mômoleth :: nominal :: house, domicile

* jûps :: verbal :: tobacco :: see /jûpsum/

* jûpsum :: nominal :: cigarette, cigar :: 

* jothorîn :: verbal ::  to smoke
  - from /jothor/ fire + /-în/ suffix meaning /I don't know what!/
  - transitive and intransitive

* wâgum :: nominal :: opium 
  -- I don't know either what /wâg/ means or why /-um/ is here

* foifir :: nominal :: cocaine 

* krêkid :: nominal :: wine 
  -- wine in particular, as wine is always mentioned in old legendary Mars stories ::
